    <sharedRules>
        <rule name="Dakka Dakka Dakka" id="d5e3-6103-fbc4-4786" hidden="false">
            <description>The unit reduces its total penalty to hit rolls in ranged combat by -1, down to a minimum of 0. Barrage and Explosive weapons do not benefit from this rule.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Mob" id="bac7-7e4d-dfdc-452d" hidden="false">
            <description>For every 5 models in your squad with this rule, the unit receives a cumulative bonus of +1 to its Leadership value. As long as a unit contains 20 or more models, it receives the "Fearless" special rule. In addition, any unit below half its target strength can join another unit with the same rule for the rest of the game. To do so, it must be within 2" of the unit it wishes to join at the start of the combat roand. From then on, both units receive only one common command.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Tellyporta" id="d4bf-c997-b14a-4707" hidden="false">
            <description>For every 1000 points of game size or part thereof, a unit may be set up for +1 point per Wound according to the rules for Deep strike. Vehicles and monstrous creatures may be set up for +4 points per Hull Point / Wound according to the rules for Deep strike. Individual models from a squadron are treated as independent units. All Ork units have this rule.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Waaagh!" id="6c83-ec4f-9356-419e" hidden="false">
            <description>The army may declare a Waaagh! once per game at the beginning of the Command phase, lasting two battle rounds. Infantry and Walkers with the "Waaagh!" rule gain an additional Movement of D6", which is not taken into account when determining which weapons they may fire. Other vehicles, Bikes and Jump pack infantry gain the "Deflect" ability instead if they have moved with their maximum possible movement value (but at least 8"). In a "Skirmish" game the effect only lasts one battle round.</description>
        </rule>
    </sharedRules>
